{
  "texts": [
    "We note a 89.3% reduction in read time (DPU-CPU), resulting in an overall improvement of 1.4×.",
    "This improvement is due to the order-of-magnitude reduction in the number of message exchanges between the VM and Firecracker, from 5000 to 125.",
    "The third bar shows the effectiveness of Request Batching.",
    "By batching write-to-rank operations, the frequency of context switches between the guest and Firecracker was reduced by two orders of magnitude, from 10000 to just 402.",
    "This optimization cut down the execution times for CPU-DPU and inter-DPU transfers by 95.8% and 95.3%, respectively.The combined version of Prefetch Cache and Request Batching yielded an overall performance boost of 10.8×."
  ]
}